The paper deals with the application of machine learning techniques to Electronic Health Records (EHR) for improving quality of care. This falls under the broad category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of metapaths and joint embedding framework, which are techniques commonly used in Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Database (cs.DB) research. Finally, the paper deals with the modeling of clinical data, which is a topic of interest in the field of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
